I always thought the notion that table salt was much saltier than cosair salt because of grain size was correct, but drunk X has inlightened me. its not correct, sure the grain size is larger inj cosair salt, but that means literally nothing, because salt is salt, and salt with a grain 5 times the size, is just as salty as 5 grains of salt thats 1/5th the size. point is, when you take into account the area that a larger grain can't take up the difference is minimal. even though a smaller grain has less gaps in between grains, the difference is minimal. but gaps in between the grain is what you should argue, not grain sizer


edit: alhough his comment about pinching IS correct.
